-- Groupon Probes U.K. Complaints After Criticism, Telegraph Says
-- B y   B e n   F a r e y
-- 2012-05-06T08:44:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-06/groupon-probes-u-k-complaints-after-criticism-telegraph-says.html
Groupon Inc. Chief Executive Officer
Andrew Mason has started weekly checks on U.K. customer
complaints after the  Office of Fair Trading  and the Advertising
Standards Authority criticized the company for violating rules
protecting consumers,  The Sunday Telegraph  said, citing Mason.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Farey in London at 
 bfarey@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
